{"timestamp": "2026-03-19T17:15:50.022686", "elapsed_seconds": 1.067, "stage": "INFO", "message": "Retrieved context for query", "data": {"context": "Document 1:\nSource: docs\\tutorial\\first-steps.md\nNavigation: First Steps > Recap, step by step > Step 3: create a *path operation*\nContent: [Context: First Steps > Recap, step by step > Step 3: create a *path operation*]\n\n### Step 3: create a [ITALIC:path operation]\n#### Path\n\"Path\" here refers to the last part of the URL starting from the first [CODE: /].\nSo, in a URL like:\n[CODE[ITALIC:BLOCK]0: https://example.com/items/foo...]\n...the path would be:\n[CODE[ITALIC:BLOCK]1: /items/foo...]\n/// info\nA \"path\" is also commonly called an \"endpoint\" or a \"route\".\n///\nWhile building an API, the \"path\" is the main way to separate \"concerns\" ...\n\nDocument 6:\nSource: docs\\tutorial\\first-steps.md\nNavigation: First Steps > Recap, step by step > Step 3: create a *path operation*\nContent: [Context: First Steps > Recap, step by step > Step 3: create a *path operation*]\n\n### Step 3: create a [ITALIC:path operation]\n#### Path\n\"Path\" here refers to the last part of the URL starting from the first [CODE: /].\nSo, in a URL like:\n[CODE[ITALIC:BLOCK]0: https://example.com/items/foo...]\n...the path would be:\n[CODE[ITALIC:BLOCK]1: /items/foo...]\n/// info\nA \"path\" is also commonly called an \"endpoint\" or a \"route\".\n///\nWhile building an API, the \"path\" is the main way to separate \"concerns\" ...\n\nDocument 11:\nSource: docs\\tutorial\\first-steps.md\nNavigation: First Steps > Recap, step by step > Step 3: create a *path operation*\nContent: [Context: First Steps > Recap, step by step > Step 3: create a *path operation*]\n\n### Step 3: create a [ITALIC:path operation]\n#### Path\n\"Path\" here refers to the last part of the URL starting from the first [CODE: /].\nSo, in a URL like:\n[CODE[ITALIC:BLOCK]0: https://example.com/items/foo...]\n...the path would be:\n[CODE[ITALIC:BLOCK]1: /ite